Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Iraqi Kurdistan Region President Nechirvan Barzani about the security situation in northern Iraq. They discussed the importance of bringing stability to disputed territories and allowing the return of displaced Iraqis, including religious and ethnic minority communities. Pence commended Barzani and the Kurdistan Regional Government for providing refuge to displaced civilians and leading efforts to protect those impacted by conflict. They also pledged to cooperate in preventing a resurgence of ISIS activity. Pence expressed concern over Iran-backed militias undermining Iraq's security and sovereignty and mentioned possible additional steps to degrade their influence. They also discussed recent progress in talks between KRG and Iraqi government officials and opportunities to deepen the US partnership with the Iraqi Kurdistan Region in the economic and security spheres.